article.headline: W. Michigan 46, E. Michigan 38
article.story: KAMALAZOO, Mich. -- David Kool scored 19 points for Western Michigan, which took a 12-point halftime lead, then held off Eastern Michigan's second-half surge for a 46-38 win Wednesday night. The Broncos out shot the Eagles from the field 55 percent (12-for-22) to 25 percent (6-for-24) in the first half to build a 27-15 halftime lead. Eastern Michigan (4-22, 2-10 Mid-American) pulled within 37-36 on Wendale Farrow's layup with 6:41 to play. But Kool scored seven points in a 9-2 Western run down the stretch to seal the win. Shawntes Gary added 10 points for the Broncos (9-16, 6-6). Kool had five rebounds. The Eagles got 13 points from Brandon Bowdry, and Justin Dobbins grabbed 12 rebounds but scored only two points on 1-7 field-goal shooting. Eastern lost despite a 33-21 rebounding edge.
